            . I have known him from the time of going that voyage. No man in the world could behave better, very honest and sober.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17700530-47-person435">
                  Thomas
                   Langham
               <interp inst="t17700530-47-person435" type="surname" value="Langham"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17700530-47-person435" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17700530-47-person435" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . He came to London better than four years ago, in order to get a clerk's place. I received him in my house; he could not meet with any thing to suit. I had occasion for somebody to write my accounts; I trusted him to sell goods, he never wronged me to my knowledge.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17700530-47-person436">
